Eugene.KNRQ:
KNRQ is a commercial alternative rock music radio station in Eugene, Oregon, broadcasting to the Eugene–Springfield, Oregon area on 103.7 FM. It has a sister station WFTK, in Cincinnati.


== Station history ==
The station signed on in April, 1974 as KOMS. On September 27, 1978 the call sign was changed to KIQY. The station was then assigned the call sign KXPC-FM by the U.S. Federal Communications Commission (FCC) on November 16, 1993.

Until May 20, 2009, KXPC-FM (then licensed to Lebanon, Oregon) broadcast a country music format branded as "Pure Country 103.7".
